SIMPLE: squally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squally
<hw>Squall"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Abounding with squalls; disturbed often with sudden and violent
gusts of wind; gusty; <as>as, <ex>squally</ex> weather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>Interrupted by unproductive
spots; -- said of a field of turnips or grain.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Weaving)</fld> <def>Not equally good throughout;
not uniform; uneven; faulty; -- said of cloth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squalodon</ent>⟦br⟧
